Asp poison has an initial damage of 113, and a DOT effect too. The giants in Frontier Mtns hate when you use this stuff.<br>
Lixt Wing Dust is useful against undead only; but it does 190 damage to them. And since it's made from embalming dust, and if you can keep resupplying your stock of it quickly enough, it's a means to its own end. Just keep applyingk, killing a mummy, applying, killing, making as you gain it. Another nice thing about that is that the cistern asps spawn in S Ro with the mummies, so you can build your asp poison stock at the same time. Many classes have no use for embalming dust, and so you can usually buy it in mass quantities from vendors in N Ro, Oasis, and S Ro. <p>Spidor (Redeemed)
